## Ingredients

### For the Lentils

- [ ] 1 cup Dried Green or Brown Lentils
- [ ] 2 1/2 cups Water or Vegetable Broth
- [ ] 1/2 tsp Salt

### For the Red Cabbage

- [ ] 2 Tbsp Olive Oil
- [ ] 1/2 head Red Cabbage, thinly sliced (about 4-5 cups)
- [ ] 2 cloves Garlic, minced
- [ ] 1/2 tsp Salt
- [ ] 1/4 tsp Black Pepper
- [ ] 1 Tbsp Balsamic Vinegar

### For the Bowl

- [ ] 2 cups Cooked Quinoa or Rice
- [ ] 1 large Avocado, sliced
- [ ] 1/4 cup Hummus or Tahini Dressing
- [ ] 2 Tbsp Pumpkin Seeds or Sunflower Seeds
- [ ] (Optional) Fresh Lemon wedges for serving
- [ ] (Optional) Fresh Parsley or Cilantro for garnish

## Recipe

1. Rinse lentils and combine with water and salt in a medium pot
1. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 20-25 minutes until tender. Drain any excess liquid
1. While lentils cook, heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat
1. Add sliced red cabbage and cook for 8-10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until softened
1. Add garlic, salt, and pepper. Cook for 1 minute
1. Stir in balsamic vinegar and cook for another 2 minutes. Remove from heat
1. Assemble bowls with quinoa or rice as the base
1. Top with cooked lentils, saut√©ed red cabbage, sliced avocado, and a dollop of hummus
1. Sprinkle with seeds and garnish with fresh herbs
1. Serve with lemon wedges for squeezing over the top

## Notes

- Can substitute chickpeas for lentils if preferred
- Add roasted sweet potatoes or butternut squash for extra heartiness
- Make components ahead and assemble bowls throughout the week
- For added protein, top with a fried or poached egg
- Tahini dressing recipe: Mix 1/4 cup tahini with 2 Tbsp lemon juice, 1 Tbsp maple syrup, water to thin, and salt to taste
